The Head of the Civil Service of the Federation (HoS), Dr. Folasade Yemi-Esan has stated that the federal government has not approved extension of service for any officer due to retire within the COVID-19 era in 2020. Yemi-Esan, in a press statement signed by the director of Information, office of the head of the civil service of the federation, Mrs. Olawunmi Ogunmosunle, warned officers against the circulation of fake circular purported to have emanated from the Office of Head of Service (OHSF) and being circulated in the social media on the subject matter. While calling on members of the public to note that the circular is fake, incorrect and did not originate from her office, she cautioned public servants especially those in the health agencies to disregard the circular in order not to fall victims to perpetrators. She said the letter head used for the circular which was titled, “Roll -over service for those due to retire within the COVID-19 era in 2020’ and dated 13th July, 2020 is not the letter- head of the OHSF and revealed that the outline of the entire circular, from the distribution list to arrangement of the sections including the grammar is completely out of sync with the way and manner circulars are issued in her office. Yemi-Esan therefore implored public servants and the public to always visit the Office website: www.ohcsf. gov.ng regularly to cross-check circulars and other information emanating from the office for authenticity. “The information on the website includes circulars issued by the office, reports on events and upcoming events among others”, she said.  